Humza Teaching

Notes

  • Distance is the magnitude of the displacement vector
    Example (Find the magnitude of a vector ).

    The magnitude of a vector is it's hypotenuse

Distance tells you "how far", displacement tells you "where"

Projectile Motion

H-Lesson

Definition (Projectile Motion).
Any object that is launched into the air, under the influence of gravity.
Ex:
1. Cannon- Will spit out cannon Ball

2.Basketball
